SIMPLE: individuate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Individuate
<hw>In`di*vid"u*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Individual</er>.]</ety> <def>Undivided.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Individuate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Individuate
<hw>In`di*vid"u*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Individuated</conjf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Individuating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To distinguish from others
of the species; to endow with individuality; to divide into individuals;
to discriminate.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> individualize.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The soul, as the prime <qex>individuating</qex> principle, and the
said reserved portion of matter as an essential and radical part of the
individuation, shall . . . make up and restore the same individual
person.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Life is <qex>individuated</qex> into infinite numbers, that have
their distinct sense and pleasure.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. H.
More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Individuation</ent>⟦br⟧
